title: Why The Olympics Aren't Fair
description:
The International Olympic Committee (IOC) has long been criticized for its Western Europe-centric orientation, a bias that influences the selection of sports offered in the Olympics. Since its inception, the IOC has primarily been led by presidents from Western Europe or the United States, which has contributed to a cultural skew in the sports recognized and promoted by the Olympic Games.

This bias is evident in the inclusion and exclusion of certain sports. For example, ice hockey, a sport with strong ties to North America and Western Europe, has been a staple in the Winter Olympics, while bandy, a sport similar to ice hockey and widely regarded as Russia's national winter sport, remains marginalized. Bandy's absence from the Olympics highlights the IOC's preference for sports rooted in Western culture, despite bandy’s significant following in Russia and Scandinavia.

Similarly, in the Summer Olympics, sports like Kabaddi, which boasts immense popularity in the Indian subcontinent, have struggled to gain recognition. Kabaddi is deeply embedded in the cultural fabric of countries like India, Pakistan, and Bangladesh, yet it is overlooked in favor of sports with stronger Western European or American roots.

This imbalance suggests that the IOC's sport selection process is heavily influenced by the cultural preferences of its leadership, leading to an Olympic program that does not fully reflect the diverse athletic traditions of the world. As a result, the global representation in the Olympics remains incomplete, leaving many culturally significant sports on the sidelines.

title: "This is not a man fighting a woman"
description:
Algerian boxer Imane Khelif and the International Olympics Committee have landed in the middle of a divide about gender in sports after her Italian competitor, Angela Carini, pulled out 46 seconds into their bout at the 2024 Paris Olympics.

Moments after, Carini fell to her knees crying, saying she quit because of the pain from Khelif’s opening punches.

Mark Adams, the spokesperson for the International Olympic Committee, told reporters Friday that there has been “a lot of misinformation around on social media particularly, which is damaging."

title: Is This Shoe So Good It's Cheating?
description:
This shoe was almost BANNED from the Olympics because it helped runners go too fast! It’s called a “supershoe” and here’s why they’re so good... 

Before “supershoes,” a good “energy return” rate was 60-65%. Now? More like 80%. WAY more of the runner’s energy that they get to reuse. These new super shoes helped runners CRUSH world records and people complained the shoes gave them an “unfair advantage”. In the end, regulators decided not to ban the shoes, just add a few limits to the design, but it’s part of a huge debate in sports about “TECH DOPING” - what tech is TOO GOOD? And what simply makes humans better?

If you like optimistic science and tech videos, subscribe for more of our show Huge If True.

title: Knock Knees
description:
Knock knees are a common presentation in people with a deep back arch.

This back arch happens when muscles at the back of the waistband get tight. This tension happens to pick up hip internal rotation by shifting the pelvis forward. 

By shifting the pelvis forward to pick up hip internal rotation, the result can be the legs coming together. This is what we see in people with knock knees. 

To straighten out your legs and improve hip mobility try this wall squat variation. To make sure your gains are consistent stop squatting before your back arches.

title: Isne Father ki tarah Support kiya hai I Simran Sharma  Amrita Rao I RJ Anmol  I Love Story #shorts
description:
Simran Sharma (born 9 November 1999) is a visually impaired paraathlete from Ghaziabad, Uttar Pradesh. She qualified to represent India at the 2024 Summer Paralympics in Paris. Sharma married Naik Gajendra Singh in November 2017. Singh is also her coach.  She is supported by sports NGO, Olympic Gold Quest.Sharma took part in the China Grand Prix and the World Para Grand Prix in Dubai in 2021. She became the first Indian para athlete to qualify for the Tokyo Paralympics in 2021, but she did not get any medals. She was selected for the Indian team to take part in the 2022 Asian Para Games in Hangzhou, China, where she won two silver medals in the 100m and 200m T12 events. At the Asian Games, she clocked 12.68 seconds for 100m on 24 October 2023 and 26.12 seconds for 200m on 26 October 2023. In today's video, RJ Anmol and Amrita have shared many things related to Simran with you. This video is truly emotional and inspiring. You should definitely watch it.

सिमरन शर्मा (जन्म 9 नवंबर 1999) गाजियाबाद, उत्तर प्रदेश से एक दृष्टिबाधित पैरा एथलीट हैं। उन्होंने पेरिस में 2024 समर पैरालिंपिक में भारत का प्रतिनिधित्व करने के लिए क्वालिफाई किया। शर्मा ने नवंबर 2017 में नायक गजेन्द्र सिंह से विवाह किया। सिंह उनके कोच भी हैं। उन्हें खेल एनजीओ, ओलंपिक गोल्ड क्वेस्ट का समर्थन प्राप्त है। शर्मा ने 2021 में चीन ग्रां प्री और दुबई में विश्व पैरा ग्रां प्री में भाग लिया। वह 2021 में टोक्यो पैरालिंपिक के लिए क्वालिफाई करने वाली पहली भारतीय पैरा एथलीट बनीं, लेकिन उन्होंने कोई पदक नहीं जीता। उन्हें 2022 में हांगझू, चीन में आयोजित एशियन पैरा गेम्स में भाग लेने के लिए भारतीय टीम में चुना गया, जहां उन्होंने 100 मीटर और 200 मीटर T12 इवेंट्स में दो रजत पदक जीते। एशियाई खेलों में उन्होंने 24 अक्टूबर 2023 को 100 मीटर के लिए 12.68 सेकंड और 26 अक्टूबर 2023 को 200 मीटर के लिए 26.12 सेकंड का समय दर्ज किया।

आज के इस वीडियो में, RJ अनमोल और अमृता ने सिमरन से जुड़ी कई बातें आपके साथ साझा की हैं। यह वीडियो सच में बहुत मार्मिक और प्रेरणादायक है। इसे आप जरूर देखें।

title: ЧИТАЙ МОЙ КОММЕНТАРИЙ 🔥 #пп #рецепты #sports #фитнес  #похудение #спорт
Why The Olympics Banned The Fastest Swimsuit
description:
This swimsuit was banned from the Olympics for making swimmers TOO FAST. You remember that year Michael Phelps won more gold medals in a single Olympics than anyone ever? He was wearing this suit!

Here’s what happened - and if you like optimistic science and tech stories, subscribe to see more.

In 2008, Speedo collaborated with NASA to make the “LZR Racer.” This suit was SO COOL. The fabric mimicked sharks’ skin with little channels that made water flow more easily. It had panels that sucked swimmers’ bodies
into a more streamlined position. And people speculated that the way it trapped air made athletes float better in the pool… which Speedo denied. 

But other brands quickly made their own “supersuits” and this new tech helped swimmers CRUSH world records. The swimming world lost their minds...

When sports gear gets TOO GOOD like this, they call it “TECH DOPING”
And if you want to know more, watch our longer episode all about it!

title: Keyshawn Davis  VS. Miguel Madueno |  HIGHLIGHTS #boxing  #sports #action #combat #fighting
description:
Lightweight contender Keyshawn Davis maintained his unbeaten record with a commanding performance against Mexico's Miguel Madueno on Saturday, featured on the undercard of the Shakur Stevenson-Artem Harutyunyan main event in Newark, New Jersey.

Madueno displayed remarkable toughness in enduring Davis' precise offense, in a bout that showcased both skill and occasional sloppiness.

From the first round, Davis (11-0, 8 KOs) showcased his superior hand speed and balance, landing punches on Madueno from close quarters. Utilizing upper-body movement and smooth footwork, Davis evaded Madueno's attempts to close the distance.

Despite Madueno's (31-3, 28 KOs) determined aggression, Davis' speed and ring control were evident. Davis effectively countered Madueno's attacks and capitalized on openings with quicker hands.

As the bout progressed, Davis capitalized on Madueno's fatigue, particularly in the later rounds. Round 7 saw Davis unleashing furious combinations, while Madueno, though resilient, began to show signs of wear.

Madueno continued to press forward with determination, even as Davis maintained control. By Round 9, Davis exploited Madueno's fatigue, landing sharp combinations at will.

Entering the final round, Davis continued his dominance with precise punches that snapped back Madueno's head. The judges unanimously scored the fight in favor of Davis, recognizing his dominance with scores of 99-91 across the board.

Davis' superiority was evident in CompuBox statistics, where he landed 49% of his punches (194 of 398), compared to Madueno's 14% (63 of 461).

Madueno's resilience was commendable, but Davis' skill and strategic prowess ultimately secured his victory in a fight marked by his technical proficiency and effective counterpunching.

title: Aprende Peque con Isa - Los Deportes para Niños- Sports - Spanish
description:
En este episodio aprende los deportes para niños con Isa. Nos mostrará diferentes juegos y deportes para entretener a nuestros peques en casa. A su vez, Isa introduce conceptos básicos y palabras nuevas a través de juegos, rimas, juguetes y canciones. Estaremos estrenando nuevas canciones "A la Víbora de la Mar", "El Sapo si se Lava el Pie" y "El Gallo Pinto". 

Isa es maestra de preescolar y educación especial, con especialización en desarrollo de lenguaje y audición. Enseña a tu peque a través de actividades, canciones y rimas en español, que promueven el desarrollo neurocognitivo, estimulan el lenguaje, habilidades sociales y emocionales e invita a usar la imaginación. Además incluye referencias de tradiciones que forman parte de la cultura latina. Sus métodos de enseñanza se basan en técnicas de terapia de lenguaje y son validadas por especialistas en el ámbito de educación infantil. 

En este episodio encontrarás a Isa enseñando: 
- Conceptos Básicos:
    - Tamaños
    - Letras
    - Partes del Cuerpo 
    - Contar 
    - Colores
    - Secuencias
- Elementos de la Rutina:
    - Comidas nutritivas
    - Cepillarse los dientes
    - Recoger y ordenar

    - Aplaudir

    - Saltar
-Deportes: 
    - Fútbol

title: Anthony Joshua  VS. Andy Ruiz - II  | Fight Highlights     #boxing #action #combat #sports #fight
description:
The 30-year-old out-boxed his opponent from start to finish, leaving Ruiz with a cut above his left eye while Joshua showed hardly any signs of the bout. Ruiz Jr., a late replacement for Jarrell Miller who had shocked Joshua in June, had been well-prepared for this fight. Joshua, having trained specifically for Ruiz, demonstrated his readiness by answering every challenge posed by his opponent.

Joshua now awaits the outcome of the February 22 rematch between Tyson Fury and Deontay Wilder, hoping to secure a fight with the winner to unify the heavyweight division. Joshua entered the ring at his lightest ever in a world title bout, weighing under 17 stone for the first time in five years to boost his speed and sharpness. Conversely, Ruiz’s weight, over 20 stone, was so unexpectedly high that it almost necessitated a reweigh.

Despite not having exceeded 280 pounds since his early professional days, Ruiz appeared unfazed by the added weight, even with the ring reportedly measuring 22 feet—two square feet more than British regulations permit. Ruiz, the challenger and a title Joshua had not held since 2016, made effective use of the additional space in the first three rounds, consistently making Ruiz miss while dancing on the outside.

Joshua was unhesitant to attack, landing a straight right that opened a sizable cut above Ruiz’s left eye in the first round, set up by his jab. Although Joshua was boxing flawlessly, Ruiz began to find his rhythm, closing the distance and delivering a damaging right hook followed by a short left in the fourth round.

Joshua, however, maintained his disciplined approach, continuing to box from the outside with his long jab and occasionally throwing a lead left hook to catch Ruiz coming in. He controlled the fight up to the halfway point, but Ruiz fought his way back, putting Joshua under pressure at close range and possibly winning his second round in the eighth.

title: Wonderful Time With Paragliding #paragliding #sports #sport #flying #gliding #paraglidingvideos
description:
Wonderful Time With Paragliding #paragliding #sports #sport #flying #gliding #paraglidingvideos 

Paragliding offers an exhilarating way to experience the beauty of the world from a unique vantage point. Whether soaring over rugged mountains, vast oceans, or lush valleys, paragliding provides a sense of freedom and adventure that is unparalleled. The thrill of lifting off the ground and gliding through the air, with the wind as your only companion, creates a memory that stays with you long after the flight ends.

One of the most wonderful aspects of paragliding is the perspective it offers. From the sky, the landscape below takes on a new dimension. Hills and forests seem to stretch endlessly, rivers snake their way through the terrain, and the horizon appears to be within reach. This bird's-eye view fosters a profound appreciation for the natural world, making the experience not only thrilling but also deeply enriching.

The sensation of paragliding is like nothing else. The gentle tug of the wind, the quiet hum of the glider as it catches the air, and the sensation of floating effortlessly combine to create an experience that feels almost otherworldly. For many, this peaceful yet exhilarating experience serves as a reminder of the beauty of life and the wonders that await when we step out of our comfort zones.

Paragliding also offers a sense of accomplishment. Whether you are a seasoned paraglider or a first-timer, the moment you land safely back on the ground, you are filled with a sense of achievement. You've conquered the sky, embraced the adventure, and experienced something truly remarkable.

In essence, a wonderful time with paragliding is about more than just the thrill of flight; it's about connecting with nature, pushing your limits, and creating unforgettable memories.

description:
Reetika Hooda: India's Last Hope for Olympic Gold 🇮🇳

Reetika Hooda is on the brink of making history once again! After becoming the first Indian to win gold at the U-23 World Championships and securing an Olympic quota in the 76kg division, Reetika now faces her biggest challenge yet.

In the upcoming round of 16, Reetika must first overcome Hungary’s Bernadett Nagy, ranked 16th in the world, and then prepare for a potential showdown with world number 1, Aiperi Medet Kyzy. With a critical transition from 72kg to 76kg, Reetika is ready to battle for India’s first Olympic gold in this category.

Catch all the action at 3 pm on August 10th! Will Reetika rise to the occasion and bring home the gold? Stay tuned and hit that subscribe button for more Olympic updates!

title: 6 Pushup Mistakes You Need to Fix!
description:
6 Pushup Mistakes You Need to Fix!

Mistake #1: Looking up, which places stress on the neck. Instead, look down so that your head stays in line with your spine.

Mistake #2: Rolling your shoulders forward at the bottom of the pushup, which causes more shoulder activation and less chest activation. Instead, roll them back.

Mistake #3: Sagging your lower body, which disrupts your form. Instead, keep your body straight and engage your core.

Mistake #4: Pointing your elbows directly to the side like a T-shape, which increases the risk of shoulder injury. Instead, keep them pointing back like an arrow shape.

Mistake #5: Moving up and down in a vertical path, which causes your elbows to flare out, increasing the risk of shoulder injury. Instead, move in a diagonal path forward. This naturally encourages you to tuck your elbows in and form an arrow shape.

Mistake #6: Elevating your shoulders, which shifts tension to your shoulders and traps, reducing chest activation. Instead, keep your shoulders down and engaged.

title: Electrostatic Levitating Ring! How does it work? #shorts #DrDawson #science
description:
A plastic ring made from a very thin grocery store bag and a plastic bat are rubbed with a piece of wool. When the wool rubs either plastic object, electrons are removed from the wool and placed on the plastic leaving the plastic negatively charged. This is called the triboelectric effect, which is the transfer of electric charge from one object to another due to friction. Now that the bat and ring are negatively charged, they repel each other. This allows us to keep the ring floating as long as we keep the bat underneath it properly.

description:
Thanks: Rolf Company
https://www.rolf.ru/
https://www.instagram.com/rolfcompany

Is the Toyota Hilux a good car?

In the world of pickup trucks, the Toyota Hilux is more like a solid, reliable workhorse than a dolled-up show pony. Its utilitarian approach to load-lugging might not be quite as attention-grabbing as the likes of the posher VW Amarok and flashy Ford Ranger, but it’s one of the most practical and affordable pickups you can buy.

Unfortunately, the Toyota Hilux’s underlying back-to-basics approach also applies to how it looks. Just try to recall what it looks like from the photo above without swiping up. Tricky, eh?

Top-spec Invincible X trucks get some more aggressive-looking bumpers with metal-effect skid plates and a sportier black grille, but even these can’t hold a candle to the lairy looking Ford Ranger Raptor.

Thankfully, the Toyota Hilux has a few tricks up its sleeve – or rather in its cabin. It looks significantly more car-like than most pickup trucks thanks to its sweeping dashboard, recessed dials and – in all but entry-level models – 7-inch touchscreen infotainment system. It’s just a shame that this display is a bit of a paint to use on the move.

Equally awkward are the cramped back seats you get in Extra Cab models. You’ll be better off saving some cash and ditching them completely or paying extra for a Double Cab Hilux that comes with a proper set of back seats.

    Entry-level versions of the Toyota Hilux are about as utilitarian as a pickup can get – just the thing for carrying loads of stuff without breaking the bank. 

Space in the load bed depends on which of these models you choose, so Single Cabs are the roomiest, followed by Extra Cab and Double Cab models. You’ll be able to carry more than a tonne in the load bed, whichever truck you pick.

There’s less choice when it comes to picking an engine for your Toyota Hilux because all versions come with a 2.4-litre four-cylinder diesel. This 150hp unit makes the Toyota Hilux far from the most powerful pickup on sale, but it has enough poke to haul you, some passengers and a decent load around without too much fuss. It’s even rated to tow a braked trailer weighing between 3200kg and 3500kg – depending on which model you choose.

Less impressive than the Toyota Hilux’s towing abilities is how it deals with bumps and tight turns. Sure, its light steering and decent forward visibility make it fairly stress-free to manoeuvre in town, but on a country road, it bounces and leans its way through corners that wouldn’t faze some more sure-footed trucks.

You don’t get cruise control as standard in entry-level models either, and it’s a shame that automatic emergency braking is reserved for mid-range models and above.

title: 2025 Toyota Hilux GR Sport - interior and Exterior Features
description:
Thanks: Rolf Company
https://www.rolf.ru/
https://www.instagram.com/rolfcompany

Is the Toyota Hilux a good car?

In the world of pickup trucks, the Toyota Hilux is more like a solid, reliable workhorse than a dolled-up show pony. Its utilitarian approach to load-lugging might not be quite as attention-grabbing as the likes of the posher VW Amarok and flashy Ford Ranger, but it’s one of the most practical and affordable pickups you can buy.

Unfortunately, the Toyota Hilux’s underlying back-to-basics approach also applies to how it looks. Just try to recall what it looks like from the photo above without swiping up. Tricky, eh?

Top-spec Invincible X trucks get some more aggressive-looking bumpers with metal-effect skid plates and a sportier black grille, but even these can’t hold a candle to the lairy looking Ford Ranger Raptor.

Thankfully, the Toyota Hilux has a few tricks up its sleeve – or rather in its cabin. It looks significantly more car-like than most pickup trucks thanks to its sweeping dashboard, recessed dials and – in all but entry-level models – 7-inch touchscreen infotainment system. It’s just a shame that this display is a bit of a paint to use on the move.

Equally awkward are the cramped back seats you get in Extra Cab models. You’ll be better off saving some cash and ditching them completely or paying extra for a Double Cab Hilux that comes with a proper set of back seats.

    Entry-level versions of the Toyota Hilux are about as utilitarian as a pickup can get – just the thing for carrying loads of stuff without breaking the bank. 

Space in the load bed depends on which of these models you choose, so Single Cabs are the roomiest, followed by Extra Cab and Double Cab models. You’ll be able to carry more than a tonne in the load bed, whichever truck you pick.

There’s less choice when it comes to picking an engine for your Toyota Hilux because all versions come with a 2.4-litre four-cylinder diesel. This 150hp unit makes the Toyota Hilux far from the most powerful pickup on sale, but it has enough poke to haul you, some passengers and a decent load around without too much fuss. It’s even rated to tow a braked trailer weighing between 3200kg and 3500kg – depending on which model you choose.

Less impressive than the Toyota Hilux’s towing abilities is how it deals with bumps and tight turns. Sure, its light steering and decent forward visibility make it fairly stress-free to manoeuvre in town, but on a country road, it bounces and leans its way through corners that wouldn’t faze some more sure-footed trucks.

You don’t get cruise control as standard in entry-level models either, and it’s a shame that automatic emergency braking is reserved for mid-range models and above.

title: IMPORTANT: Don’t forget about hamstring strengthening!!
description:
Don’t forget about the hamstrings‼️

Especially in those with arthritis, I commonly find a lot of people have hamstring weakness. This can lead to difficulty with walking, stairs, and hills ☝🏽 

Hamstring weakness can lead to other muscles compensating for example the hip. This can contribute to hip pain back pain and knee pain. This is why it’s so important to strengthen the hamstrings 🙌🏼

The hamstrings help to bend the knee and straighten the hip. These two exercises show a seated and standing variation to activate the hamstring muscles in the back of your thigh 😇

The idea is to choose one or both of these exercises and complete repetitions u lntil you begin to feel fatigue in the muscles, 10-20 may be a good place to start for most 💪🏽

If you experience cramping, relax the leg and give the muscle a short break until it resolves. Cramps can be common when weakness is present ☝🏽

If you’d like more ideas on how to make sure all of your muscles are strong and supporting the joints properly, I highly recommend giving Adventurers for Life, my arthritis workout membership a try! ✅

You’ll get step by step follow along workouts that work the FULL body- something that many programs don’t address. 

Click the link in my profile to learn more 👀

title: La vida de Kobe Bryant quedará plasmada en un cómic
description:
#N24Carabobo #entretenimiento TidalWave Comics, pionero en el mundo de los libros ilustrados biográficos, anunció este viernes que la leyenda del baloncesto Kobe Bryant será la protagonista de la última entrega de su aclamada serie ‘Tribute’, que rinde homenaje a figuras influyentes.

El cómic, escrito por Michael Frizell e ilustrado por Pablo Martinena, consta de 22 páginas y captura el notable viaje de Bryant, conocido como la ‘Mamba negra’, desde sus inicios como prodigio del baloncesto hasta convertirse en una leyenda perdurable, indica un comunicado de prensa.

‘Tribute: Kobe Bryant’ estará disponible a partir del miércoles 28 de agosto en formato digital e impreso que contará con dos ediciones, una de tapa blanda y otra tapa dura, mientras que la edición de bolsillo presentará una portada única diseñada por Martinena.

title: Whip trip
What is Sports Chiropractic
description:
Sports chiropractic focuses on diagnosing and treating injuries and disorders related to athletic activities and sports performance. Chiropractors in this field often use a variety of techniques, including spinal adjustments, soft tissue therapy, and rehabilitative exercises, to help athletes recover from injuries, enhance their performance, and maintain overall musculoskeletal health.

Here are a few key aspects of sports chiropractic:

1. **Injury Prevention and Management:** Sports chiropractors work to prevent injuries by improving biomechanical function and correcting imbalances. They also help manage and rehabilitate injuries like strains, sprains, and joint issues.

2. **Performance Enhancement:** By optimizing spinal alignment and joint function, sports chiropractors can help athletes improve their range of motion, flexibility, and strength, potentially enhancing their overall performance.

3. **Rehabilitation:** They design specific rehabilitation programs to aid recovery, focusing on restoring function, strength, and stability to the injured area.

4. **Holistic Approach:** Sports chiropractors often take a holistic approach, considering lifestyle, nutrition, and exercise habits as part of the treatment plan.

5. **Collaboration with Other Professionals:** They frequently collaborate with other healthcare professionals, such as physical therapists, sports medicine doctors, and strength and conditioning coaches, to provide comprehensive care.

If you're an athlete or involved in regular physical activity, sports chiropractic care might be beneficial in keeping you in top shape and helping you recover more effectively from injuries.  Let me know!

title: Universal Shooting Standards
description: We recently had an instructor sync up after running a few different courses. We wanted to define a set of standards we thought kept everyone accountable and was beneficial to those who wear multiple hats. The main purpose was to create a few standards to progress the groups that operate in a variety of lighting conditions and have different equipment to navigate. These are all simple drills that most everyone has done, we just wanted to unify the time standards and see what the difference was if we maintained the same body and head position but utilized a optic riser to make it more efficient and repeatable without changing our body position. Give these a try and we will keep you posted and we keep refining and add to the standards.
